    "Abstract": "Recent advances in the space of Arabic large language models have opened up a wealth of potential practical applications. We introduce AlGhafa, a new multiple-choice evaluation benchmark for Arabic LLMs. For showcasing purposes, we train a new suite of models in numerous tasks within a zero-shot framework. We also perform a qualitative and quantitative toxicity evaluation of several Arabic models, comparing our models to existing public Arabic LLMs.",
